#. type: Content of: <sections><section><title>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-alpha-bootloader.xml:15
#, no-wrap
msgid "Making your Choice"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-alpha-bootloader.xml:17
#, no-wrap
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-alpha-bootloader.xml:21
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Now that your kernel is configured and compiled and the necessary system\n"
"configuration files are filled in correctly, it is time to install a\n"
"program that will fire up your kernel when you start the system. Such a\n"
"program is called a <e>bootloader</e>. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-alpha-bootloader.xml:28
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Several bootloaders exist for Linux/Alpha. You must choose one of the supported\n"
"bootloaders, not all. You have the choice between <uri link=\"#aboot\">aBoot</uri>\n"
"and <uri link=\"#milo\">MILO</uri>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><title>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-alpha-bootloader.xml:37
#, no-wrap
msgid "Default: Using aboot"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><body><note>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-alpha-bootloader.xml:41
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<c>aboot</c> only supports booting from <b>ext2</b> and <b>ext3</b>\n"
"partitions.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><body><p>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-alpha-bootloader.xml:46
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"We first install aboot on our system. Of course we use <c>emerge</c> to\n"
"do so:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-alpha-bootloader.xml:50
#, no-wrap
msgid "Installing aboot"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-alpha-bootloader.xml:51
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>emerge aboot</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><body><p>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-alpha-bootloader.xml:55
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The next step is to make our bootdisk bootable. This will start\n"
"<c>aboot</c> when you boot your system. We make our bootdisk bootable by\n"
"writing the <c>aboot</c> bootloader to the start of the disk.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-alpha-bootloader.xml:60
#, no-wrap
msgid "Making your bootdisk bootable"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-alpha-bootloader.xml:61
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>swriteboot -f3 /dev/sda /boot/bootlx</i> \n"
"# <i>abootconf /dev/sda 2</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><body><note>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-alpha-bootloader.xml:66
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you use a different partitioning scheme than the one we use\n"
"throughout this chapter, you have to change the commands accordingly.\n"
"Please read the appropriate manual pages (<c>man 8 swriteboot</c> and\n"
"<c>man 8 abootconf</c>). Also, if your root filesystem is ran using the JFS\n"
"filesystem, make sure it gets mounted read-only at first by adding <c>ro</c> as\n"
"a kernel option.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><body><p>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-alpha-bootloader.xml:75
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Although <c>aboot</c> is now installed, we still need to write a configuration\n"
"file for it. Aboot only requires one line for each configuration, so we\n"
"can do this:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-alpha-bootloader.xml:80
#, no-wrap
msgid "Creating /etc/aboot.conf"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-alpha-bootloader.xml:81
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>echo '0:2/boot/vmlinux.gz root=/dev/sda2' &gt; /etc/aboot.conf</i>\n"
"\n"
"<comment>\n"
"If, while building the Linux kernel, you opted to include an initramfs to boot\n"
"from, then you will need to change the configuration by referring to this\n"
"initramfs file and telling the initramfs where your real root device is at:\n"
"</comment>\n"
"\n"
"# <i>echo '0:2/boot/vmlinux.gz initrd=/boot/<keyval id=\"genkernel-initrd\"/> real_root=/dev/sda2' &gt; /etc/aboot.conf</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><body><p>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-alpha-bootloader.xml:94
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Additionally, you can make Gentoo boot automatically by setting up some SRM\n"
"variables. You can try setting these variables from Linux, but it may be easier\n"
"to do so from the SRM console itself.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-alpha-bootloader.xml:99
#, no-wrap
msgid "Automatically booting Gentoo"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-alpha-bootloader.xml:100
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>cd /proc/srm_environment/named_variables</i>\n"
"# <i>echo -n 0 &gt; boot_osflags</i>\n"
"# <i>echo -n '' &gt; boot_file</i>\n"
"# <i>echo -n 'BOOT' &gt; auto_action</i>\n"
"# <i>echo -n 'dkc100' &gt; bootdef_dev</i>\n"
"<comment>(Substitute dkc100 with whatever your boot device is)</comment>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><body><p>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-alpha-bootloader.xml:109
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you need to get into the SRM console again in the future (to recover \n"
"your Gentoo install, play with some variables, or whatever), just hit \n"
"CTRL+C to abort the automatic loading process.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><body><p>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-alpha-bootloader.xml:115
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you're installing using a serial console, don't forget to include \n"
"the serial console boot flag in <path>aboot.conf</path>.  See  \n"
"<path>/etc/aboot.conf.example</path> for some further information.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><body><p>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-alpha-bootloader.xml:121
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Aboot is now configured and ready to use. Continue with <uri\n"
"link=\"#reboot\">Rebooting the System</uri>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><title>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-alpha-bootloader.xml:128
#, no-wrap
msgid "Alternative: Using MILO"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><body><p>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-alpha-bootloader.xml:132
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Before continuing, you should decide on how to use MILO. In this\n"
"section, we will assume that you want to make a MILO boot floppy. If you\n"
"are going to boot from an MS-DOS partition on your hard disk, you should\n"
"amend the commands appropriately.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><body><p>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-alpha-bootloader.xml:139
#, no-wrap
msgid "To install MILO, we use <c>emerge</c>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-alpha-bootloader.xml:142
#, no-wrap
msgid "Installing MILO"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-alpha-bootloader.xml:143
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>emerge milo</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><body><p>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-alpha-bootloader.xml:147
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"After MILO has been installed, the MILO images should be in\n"
"<path>/opt/milo</path>. The commands below make a bootfloppy for use\n"
"with MILO. Remember to use the correct image for your Alpha-system.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-alpha-bootloader.xml:152
#, no-wrap
msgid "Installing MILO on a floppy"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-alpha-bootloader.xml:153
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<comment>(First insert a blank floppy)</comment>\n"
"# <i>fdformat /dev/fd0</i>\n"
"# <i>mformat a:</i>\n"
"# <i>mcopy /opt/milo/milo-2.4-18-gentoo-ruffian a:\\milo</i>\n"
"# <i>mcopy /opt/milo/linload.exe a:\\linload.exe</i>\n"
"<comment>(Only if you have a Ruffian:</comment>     \n"
"  # <i>mcopy /opt/milo/ldmilo.exe a:\\ldmilo.exe</i>\n"
"<comment>)</comment>\n"
"# <i>echo -ne '\\125\\252' | dd of=/dev/fd0 bs=1 seek=510 count=2</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><body><p>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-alpha-bootloader.xml:165
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Your MILO boot floppy is now ready to boot Gentoo Linux. You may need to\n"
"set environment variables in your ARCS Firmware to get MILO to start;\n"
"this is all explained in the <uri\n"
"link=\"http://tldp.org/HOWTO/MILO-HOWTO/\">MILO-HOWTO</uri> with some examples \n"
"on common systems, and examples of the commands to use in interactive mode.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><body><p>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-alpha-bootloader.xml:173
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Not reading the <uri link=\"http://tldp.org/HOWTO/MILO-HOWTO/\">MILO-HOWTO</uri> \n"
"is a <e>bad</e> idea.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><body><p>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-alpha-bootloader.xml:178
#, no-wrap
msgid "Now continue with <uri link=\"#reboot\">Rebooting the System</uri>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><title>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-alpha-bootloader.xml:184
#, no-wrap
msgid "Rebooting the System"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-alpha-bootloader.xml:189
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Exit the chrooted environment and unmount all mounted partitions. Then type in \n"
"that one magical command you have been waiting for: <c>reboot</c>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-alpha-bootloader.xml:193
#, no-wrap
msgid "Exiting the chroot, unmounting all partitions and rebooting"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-alpha-bootloader.xml:194
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>exit</i>\n"
"cdimage ~# <i>cd</i>\n"
"cdimage ~# <i>umount -l /mnt/gentoo/dev{/shm,/pts,}</i>\n"
"cdimage ~# <i>umount -l /mnt/gentoo{/boot,/proc,}</i>\n"
"cdimage ~# <i>reboot</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-alpha-bootloader.xml:202
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Of course, don't forget to remove the bootable CD, otherwise the CD will be\n"
"booted again instead of your new Gentoo system.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-alpha-bootloader.xml:207
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Once rebooted in your Gentoo installation, finish up with <uri\n"
"link=\"?part=1&amp;chap=11\">Finalizing your Gentoo Installation</uri>.\n"
msgstr ""
